title: True Grit
overview: A stubborn teenager enlists the help of a tough U.S. Marshal to track down her father's murderer.

title: Django Unchained
overview: With the help of a German bounty hunter, a freed slave sets out to rescue his wife from a brutal Mississippi plantation owner.

title: Giant
overview: Sprawling epic covering the life of a Texas cattle rancher and his family and associates.

title: High Noon
overview: A town Marshal, despite the disagreements of his newlywed bride and the townspeople around him, must face a gang of deadly killers alone at high noon when the gang leader, an outlaw he sent up years ago, arrives on the noon train.

title: Gifted
overview: Frank, a single man raising his child prodigy niece Mary, is drawn into a custody battle with his mother.

title: Giù la testa
overview: A low-life bandit and an I.R.A. explosives expert rebel against the government and become heroes of the Mexican Revolution.

title: Festen
overview: At Helge's 60th birthday party, some unpleasant family truths are revealed.

title: The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance
overview: A senator returns to a western town for the funeral of an old friend and tells the story of his origins.

title: Lifeboat
overview: Several survivors of a torpedoed merchant ship in World War II find themselves in the same lifeboat with one of the crew members of the U-boat that sank their ship.

title: Philadelphia
overview: When a man with HIV is fired by his law firm because of his condition, he hires a homophobic small time lawyer as the only willing advocate for a wrongful dismissal suit.

title: Höstsonaten
overview: A married daughter who longs for her mother's love is visited by the latter, a successful concert pianist.

title: Mommy
overview: A widowed single mother, raising her violent son alone, finds new hope when a mysterious neighbor inserts herself into their household.

title: Mysterious Skin
overview: A teenage hustler and a young man obsessed with alien abductions cross paths, together discovering a horrible, liberating truth.

title: Hamlet
overview: Hamlet, Prince of Denmark, returns home to find his father murdered and his mother remarrying the murderer, his uncle. Meanwhile, war is brewing.

title: Zwartboek
overview: In the Nazi-occupied Netherlands during World War II, a Jewish singer infiltrates the regional Gestapo headquarters for the Dutch resistance.

title: Gran Torino
overview: Disgruntled Korean War veteran Walt Kowalski sets out to reform his neighbor, Thao Lor, a Hmong teenager who tried to steal Kowalski's prized possession: a 1972 Gran Torino.

title: Creed
overview: The former World Heavyweight Champion Rocky Balboa serves as a trainer and mentor to Adonis Johnson, the son of his late friend and former rival Apollo Creed.

title: Magnolia
overview: An epic mosaic of interrelated characters in search of love, forgiveness, and meaning in the San Fernando Valley.

title: American History X
overview: A former neo-nazi skinhead tries to prevent his younger brother from going down the same wrong path that he did.

title: Jagten
overview: A teacher lives a lonely life, all the while struggling over his son's custody. His life slowly gets better as he finds love and receives good news from his son, but his new luck is about to be brutally shattered by an innocent little lie.
